    <link type="guide" xref="index#common-tasks"/>
    <desc>Create, enter, and remove isolated project workspaces.</desc>
  </info>

  <title>Create and manage workspaces</title>

  <p>Each workspace is an isolated project folder mapped into the shared
  <code>podbx-os</code> container. Nothing you install inside a workspace
  touches your real system.</p>

  <steps>
    <item><p>Click <gui>New Workspace</gui> and give it a name.</p></item>
    <item><p>Click <gui>Open Terminal</gui> to drop into a container shell
    at that workspace, or <gui>Open With</gui> to launch an IDE there.</p></item>
    <item><p>Click the trash icon to delete a workspace directory. The
    shared base container is never affected.</p></item>
  </steps>

</page>
